## Signal inventory

All topics live in PX4 uORB. Sample rates listed are typical — confirm in your logs with `pyulog`.

### A. Inner rate loop — `τ_cmd → ω_meas`

| Role | uORB topic | Field(s) | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Input — normalized torque** (post-PID, pre-allocation) | `vehicle_torque_setpoint` | `xyz[3]` ∈ [-1, 1] | Published by `mc_rate_control` at ~gyro rate. Source: `src/modules/mc_rate_control/MulticopterRateControl.cpp:287` |
| **Input — per-motor command** (post-allocation) | `actuator_motors` | `control[0..N]` ∈ [0,1], `NaN` for stopped | Published by `control_allocator` at ~250 Hz. Source: `src/modules/control_allocator/ControlAllocator.cpp:679` |
| **Output — measured body rate** | `vehicle_angular_velocity` | `xyz[3]` rad/s | Bias-corrected, filtered gyro. ~250–1000 Hz depending on `IMU_GYRO_RATEMAX`. Source: `src/modules/sensors/vehicle_angular_velocity/VehicleAngularVelocity.cpp:933` |
| Output — measured angular accel (validation) | `vehicle_angular_velocity` | `xyz_derivative[3]` rad/s² | Useful for inertia checks / second-derivative sanity. |
| Reference (closed-loop) | `vehicle_rates_setpoint` | `roll`, `pitch`, `yaw` | In Acro this is generated from sticks inside `mc_rate_control` (`MulticopterRateControl.cpp:184-205`). |
| Saturation flag | `control_allocator_status` | `unallocated_torque[3]`, `torque_setpoint_achieved` | **Discard data windows where this is non-zero** — your input is no longer the true plant excitation when allocator saturates. |
| Diagnostic | `rate_ctrl_status` | `rollspeed_integ`, `pitchspeed_integ`, `yawspeed_integ` | Integrator state, helps when validating that integral term isn't biasing the response. |

Why log **both** torque-setpoint and per-motor commands: `vehicle_torque_setpoint` gives you a clean 3-axis input but lumps motor + allocator dynamics into the plant. `actuator_motors` lets you (a) compute the actual body torques via the effectiveness matrix and (b) verify the allocator isn't shaping/clipping your excitation. Compare the two FRFs — a divergence above ~10 Hz typically points at allocator slew limits.

### B. Outer attitude loop — `ω_sp → q_meas`

| Role | uORB topic | Field(s) | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Input — commanded rates** (controller output) | `vehicle_rates_setpoint` | `roll`, `pitch`, `yaw` rad/s | Published by `mc_att_control` at ~100 Hz on attitude-tick. Source: `src/modules/mc_att_control/mc_att_control_main.cpp:326` |
| **Output — measured attitude** | `vehicle_attitude` | `q[4]` quaternion | From EKF2, ~100 Hz. Source: `src/modules/ekf2/EKF2.cpp:983`. Convert to Euler or to axis-angle error vector for per-axis Bode. |
| Output — measured rates (alt. for tight inner loop) | `vehicle_angular_velocity` | `xyz[3]` rad/s | If inner loop is fast (BW ≫ outer BW), you can approximate `ω_meas ≈ ω_sp` and use this as the cleaner "attitude derivative". |
| Reference (closed-loop) | `vehicle_attitude_setpoint` | `q_d[4]` quaternion | Published by `mc_pos_control` in auto modes, or generated inside `mc_att_control::generate_attitude_setpoint()` (line 112) in Stabilized. |
| Reset flags | `vehicle_attitude` | `quat_reset_counter`, `delta_q_reset[4]` | **Drop windows where this counter increments** — heading discontinuities will pollute the FRF. |

### C. Cascade end-to-end — `q_d → q_meas`

Same topics as B, but use `vehicle_attitude_setpoint.q_d` as input and `vehicle_attitude.q` as output. The simplest signal to derive a meaningful Bode is the attitude error vector `eq = 2·imag(q.inversed() * q_d)` (axis-angle / sin(α/2) representation) — this is exactly what `AttitudeControl::update()` computes at `src/modules/mc_att_control/AttitudeControl/AttitudeControl.cpp:84-88`, so you can post-process it identically per axis.

### D. Common context channels (log in every experiment)

| Topic | Use |
|---|---|
| `manual_control_setpoint` | The pilot's actual stick input — independent record of the doublet you flew. |
| `vehicle_control_mode` | Confirms which mode was active (`flag_control_attitude_enabled`, `flag_control_rates_enabled`, `flag_control_manual_enabled`). |
| `vehicle_status` | Arming state, vehicle type. |
| `vehicle_land_detected` | Drop ground-contact windows. |
| `battery_status` | Voltage compensation — thrust constant drifts with V_batt. |
| `vehicle_local_position` | (optional) For checking whether velocity / altitude was varying enough to cause inertia / throttle bias. |

