## Logging configuration

Set the logging profile bitmask to enable Default + System-ID + High-Rate:

```
param set SDLOG_PROFILE 25     # 1 (Default) + 8 (System_ID) + 16 (High_Rate)
param set SDLOG_MODE 0         # Log while armed (default)
param save
reboot
```

What each bit gives:

- **Default (1)** — `vehicle_attitude`, `actuator_motors`, `vehicle_status`, `battery_status`, etc.
- **System_ID (8)** — `sensor_combined`, `vehicle_angular_velocity`, `vehicle_torque_setpoint` at full rate. Source: `src/modules/logger/logged_topics.cpp:456-462`.
- **High_Rate (16)** — `manual_control_setpoint`, `vehicle_attitude_setpoint`, `vehicle_rates_setpoint`, `rate_ctrl_status`, `vehicle_thrust_setpoint`, `actuator_outputs`. Source: `src/modules/logger/logged_topics.cpp:319-350`.

**Verify** that `actuator_motors` is actually being logged at high rate — if it falls under interval-throttling in the Default profile, add an explicit override via custom topics file at `/fs/microsd/etc/logging/logger_topics.txt`:

```
actuator_motors 0 0          # 0 ms interval = full rate, instance 0
control_allocator_status 0 0
```

Loaded by `LoggedTopics::add_topics_from_file()` at `src/modules/logger/logged_topics.cpp:469`.

