## Experiment matrix

| Experiment | Mode | Sticks | Plant identified | Input signal | Output signal |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Roll rate FRF | **Acro** | Roll doublets / 3-2-1-1, throttle fixed | `τ_x → p` | `vehicle_torque_setpoint.xyz[0]` (and `actuator_motors` for cross-check) | `vehicle_angular_velocity.xyz[0]` |
| Pitch rate FRF | Acro | Pitch doublets | `τ_y → q` | `.xyz[1]` | `.xyz[1]` |
| Yaw rate FRF | Acro | Yaw doublets | `τ_z → r` | `.xyz[2]` | `.xyz[2]` |
| Roll attitude FRF | **Stabilized** | Roll-stick doublets, throttle hover | `ω_x,sp → φ` | `vehicle_rates_setpoint.roll` | Euler-roll from `vehicle_attitude.q` |
| Pitch attitude FRF | Stabilized | Pitch doublets | `ω_y,sp → θ` | `.pitch` | Euler-pitch |
| Cascade roll | Stabilized | Roll doublets | `φ_sp → φ` | Euler-roll from `vehicle_attitude_setpoint.q_d` | Euler-roll from `vehicle_attitude.q` |
| Cascade pitch | Stabilized | Pitch doublets | `θ_sp → θ` | Euler-pitch from `q_d` | Euler-pitch from `q` |

**Doublet design** (per axis): a chain of 8–15 doublets with increasing frequency, e.g. periods 4 s → 0.1 s (≈ 0.25–10 Hz). This is the standard CIFER-style frequency-sweep substitute for non-parametric ID. ~60–90 s total per axis. Keep amplitudes small enough that allocator saturation flags stay zero.

