## Post-processing recipe (per axis, per FRF)

1. Read `.ulg` with `pyulog`. Resample all signals to a common 200–400 Hz grid using `timestamp_sample` (not `timestamp` — the former is the source-data time, the latter is publication time and has jitter).
2. Mask out segments where any of these is true: `vehicle_land_detected.landed`, `control_allocator_status.torque_setpoint_achieved == false`, `vehicle_attitude.quat_reset_counter` changed.
3. Detrend input/output (remove mean, optionally linear trend).
4. Welch's method for cross- and auto-spectra:
   - `G(f) = S_uy(f) / S_uu(f)` (estimated FRF)
   - `γ²(f) = |S_uy(f)|² / (S_uu(f)·S_yy(f))` (coherence — trust only bins with γ² > ~0.6)
5. Plot magnitude/phase Bode. Repeat for `vehicle_torque_setpoint`-input vs `actuator_motors`-projected-input and compare.

Python libs that work out of the box: `scipy.signal.csd`, `scipy.signal.coherence`, or `control.frequency_response` if fitting a TF afterward.

